# Frontend Styling (SCSS/Sass)

Styling is SCSS/Sass based. Do not introduce Tailwind.

## Structure

- Co-locate component styles (`Component.module.scss`) with components.
- Keep shared tokens and mixins in dedicated partials.
- Prefer CSS Modules for component isolation.

## Naming and selectors

- Prefer class-based selectors.
- Use clear BEM-like naming where it improves clarity.
- Keep nesting shallow (ideally <= 3 levels).

## Reuse and responsiveness

- Reuse variables and mixins over hard-coded values.
- Keep breakpoints centralized in variables/mixins.
- Avoid inline styles for layout except when truly necessary.
